column1: On September 9, 2013, the Federal Reserve conducted a fixed-rate offering of term deposits with full allotment of tenders through its Term Deposit Facility. The operation offered 28-day term deposits at an interest rate of 0.26000 percent. Following are the results of the operation:
column4: The awarded deposits will settle on September 12, 2013, and will mature on October 10, 2013. The interest rate of 0.26000 percent will apply to all awarded deposits.
